<worksheet >
    <title>TF-4 Laws of Sines and Cosines</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both parts to get M. Complete part a with progress on part b to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in">
      <introduction><p>A naval ship travels 20 miles in the direction <m>\text{S } 35^\circ \text{ W}</m> 
        to avoid a shallow reef. It then changes its course to a bearing of 
        <m>\text{S } 72^\circ \text{ W}</m> to reach a specific coordinate marker. A tracking station, 
        located due west of the ship's starting point, notes that the marker is located due south of 
        its tracking dishes.</p></introduction>
        <task><statement><p>Draw a diagram to model this situation.</p></statement></task>
        <task><statement><p>Find the total distance the ship traveled on both legs of its journey. Give 
          a simplified expression for your answer.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>